long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: When I tried to proceed according to test case: http://fedoraproject.org/wiki/QA:Testcase_partitioning_custom_software_RAID in blivet-gui in anaconda, I found, that the ordering of partitions was very strange. I found very problematic to have /boot and /boot/efi as last partitions.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): anaconda-26.21.1-1.fc26 Fedora-secondary 26 Alpha aarch64
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. http://fedoraproject.org/wiki/QA:Testcase_partitioning_custom_software_RAID
Actual results: /boot and /boot/efi are on last partitions, it's not possible to change ordering
Expected results: /boot and /boot/efi are on first partitions
Additional info: It would be very good to have ability to change ordering of partitions manually, but that seems to be more like big RFE in current situation.

Created attachment 1269285 screenshot.png
Forgot to attach screenshot.
This is also issue for x86_64 with UEFI.
